LinkedListNode Index¶

class LinkedListNode(nodeData, nodeReference, nodeNext)¶

class to initialize a linked list node

Class constructor

Arguments:
  • nodeData (Object) – the data value for the node
  • nodeReference (reference) – The reference value for the pointer
  • nodeNext (reference) – The reference value for the next node in the chain
LinkedListNode.difference(OtherNode, diff, index)¶

Calculats the difference between this linkedlist node and the other linkedlist node

Arguments:
  • OtherNode (LinkedListNode) – The other linked list that will be compared with this linked list
  • diff (Hash) – Hash table
  • index (Integer) – the node index
LinkedListNode.equals(OtherNode)¶

checks if the current node is equal to the other node

Arguments:
  • OtherNode (LinkedListNode) – the other node that will be compared to the current node
